WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.719
Hi everyone, my name is Yihui, and I'm very excited to teach the workshop titled Advanced

00:00:16.719 --> 00:00:25.879
R Markdown, and I will be joined by my co-lecturer Alison Hill, and I also will have two guest

00:00:25.879 --> 00:00:33.160
lecturers, Jenna Gu and Hao Zhu. This will be a two-day hands-on workshop, primarily

00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:40.400
based on our recent book, R Markdown, the Definitive Guide. This work is designed for

00:00:40.400 --> 00:00:46.320
those who want to improve their R Markdown skills. In particular, we will talk about

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:53.619
many low-level details that you probably don't hear very often. For example, how to tweak

00:00:53.619 --> 00:01:00.680
the appearance of your HTML documents, PDF documents, or Word, or PowerPoint presentations.

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:07.419
So that is about how to customize your R Markdown output. And the second part, you will learn

00:01:07.419 --> 00:01:16.739
some existing R packages, including flexdashboard for creating dashboards, bookdown for writing

00:01:16.739 --> 00:01:25.379
books, blogdown for building websites, pkgdown for building websites for your R packages,

00:01:25.379 --> 00:01:32.379
and articles for writing journal articles, and learner for building interactive tutorials.

00:01:32.379 --> 00:01:39.660
We will also talk about some other features, including how to use or develop new language

00:01:39.660 --> 00:01:45.820
engines, meaning that you don't have to use R in R Markdown, you can also use Python or

00:01:45.820 --> 00:01:53.620
C++. And we will also briefly talk about some interactive components of R Markdown, including

00:01:53.620 --> 00:02:03.900
HTML widgets and also Shiny documents. I gave a three-hour workshop on this topic in 2017,

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:08.979
in which I didn't really have enough time to explain all the details, so this time I

00:02:08.979 --> 00:02:17.139
will be very excited to show you a lot more details in this workshop. I really look forward

00:02:17.139 --> 00:02:21.580
to seeing all of you at the conference, and I hope you will learn a lot.

